16. Requests the Committee to:
    (a) Establish and maintain updated lists of entry and landing areas for aircraft under Taliban control;
    (b) Establish and maintain updated lists of individuals and entities associated with Usama bin Laden;
    (c) Consider requests for exceptions;
    (d) Establish a list of approved organizations and governmental relief agencies;
    (e) Make relevant information publicly available;
    (f) Consider a visit to countries in the region;
    (g) Make periodic reports to the Council;

17. Calls upon all States and organizations to act strictly in accordance with this resolution;

18. Calls upon States to bring proceedings against persons and entities that violate the measures imposed;

19. Calls upon all States to cooperate fully with the Committee;

20. Requests all States to report to the Committee within 30 days on steps taken to implement this resolution;

21. Requests the Secretariat to submit information on possible violations;

22. Decides that the measures imposed shall come into force at 00:01 Eastern Standard Time, one month after adoption;

23. Decides that the measures are established for 12 months and will be reviewed;

24. Decides to terminate the measures if the Taliban comply with conditions before the 12-month period elapses.
1333 (2000)

25. Expresses readiness to consider further measures to achieve full implementation of this resolution and resolution 1267 (1999), taking into account the impact assessment in paragraph 15 (d) to enhance sanctions' effectiveness and avoid humanitarian consequences;

26. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
